p :::s15:::Adam tells Brint about his girlfriend , the mischievous , talkative , but ultimately sensitive Amy .
:::s16:::He remembers a day Amy called to tell him that , while at her father 's newspaper office , an editor had dropped in for a visit from Rawlings , Pennsylvania , where Adam had told her his family had moved from .
p :::s18:::Adam lied to Amy that they only lived in Rawlings for a few months , but he became more curious about his family 's past .
p :::s32:::Before leaving Carver , Adam places a call to Amy .
:::s33:::A man answers and says there is no Amy at his residence .
p :::s75:::He calls Amy on a pay phone .
